\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Download and install the LPD8 Editor \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.akaipro.com/product/lpd8#downloads"}}{\fldrslt http://www.akaipro.com/product/lpd8#downloads}}\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Note: Explaining the Editor in detail is beyond the scope of this tutorial. Checkout the Quick Installation guide if you have any questions about the Editor. \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	2.	}When you launch the Editor a midiInfo dialog window will prompt you to select the LPD8. Do this and click done. \
{\listtext	3.	}We will be changing CC# for PAD7 and PAD8 to 7 and 8 as well as changing the value of CC for K1 - K8 to 9 - 16\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}This change is made prevent the Pad Controller Values from accidentally messing with the Knob Controller values when you are have CC selected on the controller.  \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	4.	}To change the CC# for Pad7 click on the arrow or number 8 next to CC#\
{\listtext	5.	}The arrow should turn white and you can now type in the new value. In this tutorial we will be using the number 7 however you could use any number between 0 and 127. \
{\listtext	6.	}Repeat this process for Pad8 using the number 8 instead of the number 7\
{\listtext	7.	}Now to change the CC value for the knobs. \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Note: K1 is the top left knob in this example\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	8.	}Select CC for K1. You can do this be clicking the arrow or the number 1\
{\listtext	9.	}The arrow should turn white and you can now type in the new value. In this tutorial we will be using the number 9 however you could use any number between 0 and 127.\
{\listtext	10.	}Repeat this process for Knobs K2 through K8 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Once you have finished changing the values for the knobs you will be able to get different CC values for the buttons (by pressing/hitting) and the knobs (by turning)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	11.	}Preset 1 is now done. Now select Preset 2 from the top right of the Editor. \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Notice when you select Preset 2 the CC# and CC values change back to what they originally were. \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	12.	}We will now set the CC# and CC values in Preset 2 to those of Preset 1.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Follow steps 4 through 10\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	13.	}Once you have set all of the values for Preset 2 press the Commit - Upload button. \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}An dialog box should open that informs you the upload was a success \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	14.	}Congratulations, this is it for the first preset! \
