\cf0 So what exactly does this preset do? \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}We have Two Program Presets which gives us the following values to work with\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG1 and PAD selected we have 8 Pitch and 8 Velocity Values which are accessible through using the pads. \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG2 and PAD selected we have 8 Pitch and 8 Velocity Values which are accessible through using the pads. \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG1 and CC selected we have 16 Controller Values which are accessible through pads and knobs. 8 pad values which are velocity based (how hard you strike the pad) and 8 knob values which are based on the knobs position from min to max. The Knob values can be accessed in PAD, CC, and PROG CHNG\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG2 and CC selected we have 16 Controller Values which are accessible through pads and knobs. 8 pad values which are velocity based (how hard you strike the pad) and 8 knob values which are based on the knobs position from min to max The Knob values can be accessed in PAD, CC, and PROG CHNG\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG1 and PROG CHNG selected we have 8 Program Change values which are accessible through the pads\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}With PROG2 and PROG CHNG selected we have 8 Program Change values which are accessible through the pads\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	2.	}In Max/MSP with this information you could get 32 toggle values, 16 Velocity based triggers, and 16 knob values. \
